 can cause cell death, particularly in primary cells. We highly recommend treating your IVT sgRNA with recombinant Shrimp Alkaline Phosphatase (rSAP) before proceeding to the purification step. We found that rSAP treatment must be rigorous to completely remove all 5-PPP groups from your RNA. However, rSAP binds tightly to RNA and NEB recommends to only use the minimal amount needed.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1090091,"guid":"4407CF593E1644B4BA09D8A98EBF49BA","previous_id":1090090,"previous_guid":"57DCE0A2FB9D4840A660261F2422CF07","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4A67FD4F77044303813E029C564D6507","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Removal of 5'-triphosphate groups"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4EEF861E0FE740BF8EBE819CE05F9A95","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 3ul of NEB CutSmart Buffer (comes with the rSAP enzyme)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 4\u00b5l of H2O<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 2ul (2 units) of rSAP<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"2C5316F03A1111EB86ECD1F561240BE8","order_id":2,"type_id":20,"title":"reagents","source":{"id":1133,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Shrimp Alkaline Phosphatase (rSAP) - 500 units","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.neb.com\/M0371","sku":"M0371S","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"New England Biolabs","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.neb.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/2.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/2.png"},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":2},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1090092,"guid":"7D5A1A8AD20345B78F60375EEDF29426","previous_id":1090091,"previous_guid":"4407CF593E1644B4BA09D8A98EBF49BA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C8737B32A10944479DC84266D6688112","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Removal of 5'-triphosphate groups"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"050CEAC105344CAA92773F586A14C4F5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Mix well and incubate at 37C for 3h<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"990A631DA98240FC9D70A60D1671DBFF","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":10800,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"E05AF32422294B10B270862B5E5935CE","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":37,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1090093,"guid":"D206651639F3428C980CBAC0091BD27A","previous_id":1090092,"previous_guid":"7D5A1A8AD20345B78F60375EEDF29426","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C8BE58B5AB034BF099D0556F1071ED84","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"sgRNA purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A08FD6FF28E14E1085F63792ADDCDDAA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">sgRNAs need to be purfied before transfection. There are different methods one could purify their sgRNAs. We found that while SPRI bead clean-up of RNAs is quick and gives reliable yields (see older versions of protocol), SPRI bead purified sgRNAs still cause an elevated immune response even after Phosphatase treatment. We therefore tested different column purification kits and found that column purification of sgRNAs completely eliminates the immune response after Phosphatase treatment.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">We use the Qiagen RNeasy Mini Prep Kit and follow the manufacturer's instructions with the following modifications:<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"3BA0D4FFCD2B481596EDD3371C15E2FF","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Yields of from column purification can be low as the sgRNAs are small and most kits are designed to bind longer RNAs. We found the Qiagen RNeasy kit works ok, but others recommend the miRNeasy kit from Qiagen. It might be worth trying a few different kits to optimize your yield. <\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1090094,"guid":"AC0E5F63E4864892965A874D2BCBA9E9","previous_id":1090093,"previous_guid":"D206651639F3428C980CBAC0091BD27A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"97040FBBC30C42588E7E850B5D7B3EDA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"sgRNA purification"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E9DCE291086340E195DB457567470394","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Adjust sgRNA sample to a volume of 100 \u00b5l with RNase-free water.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 350 \u00b5l RLT Buffer to the sample <\/d